ly converts to Islam were the poor, foreigners and former slaves like Bilal ibn Rabah al-Habashi who was black.", "Sunni Islam and Shia Islam thus differ in some respects.The Umayyad dynasty conquered the Maghreb, the Iberian Peninsula, Narbonnese Gaul and Sindh.", "However, Islamic law would not be codified until 1869.", "The Ghaznavid dynasty was an Islamic dynasty established by Turkic slave-soldiers from another Islamic empire, the Samanid Empire.Two Turkish tribes, the Karahanids and the Seljuks, converted to Islam during the 10th century.", "Conversion to Islam, however, was not a sudden abandonment of old religious practices; rather, it was typically a matter of \"assimilating Islamic rituals, cosmologies, and literatures into... local religious systems.\"", "Throughout this expanse, Islam blended with local cultures everywhere, as illustrated when the prophet Muhammad appeared in Hindu epics and folklore.", "Under the Ottoman Empire, Islam spread to Southeast Europe.", "The wealthy Islamic Bengal Sultanate was subsequently founded, a major global trading nation in the world, described by the Europeans to be the \"richest country to trade with\".", "Liberal Islam is a movement that attempts to reconcile religious tradition with modern norms of secular governance and human rights.", "Islamist groups such as the Muslim Brotherhood advocate Islam as a comprehensive political solution, often in spite of being banned.", "In Turkey, the Islamist AK Party has democratically been in power for about a decade, while Islamist parties did well in elections following the Arab Spring.", "The Organisation of Islamic Cooperation, consisting of Muslim-majority countries, was established in 1969 after the burning of the Al-Aqsa Mosque in Jerusalem.Religiosity appears to be deepening worldwide.", "Shia Islam has several branches, the most prominent being the Twelvers, Zaidis and Ismailis.", "Mahdavia is an Islamic sect that believes in a 15th-century Mahdi, Muhammad Jaunpuri\nT